While galavanting around The Bronx and feeling thirsty, I typed in -smoothies- in my trusty Yelp search bar. Green Juice Cafe popped up in the query and I did not hesitate a second to start driving directions to it. The 5-star reviews spotted me (sold me on the spot).  A 15mins drive later and my sister and I entered this cute little shop. We were greeted by a beautiful smiling woman; Victoria. Whom I approached and told her it was our first time there. She was delighted to assist me in choosing what to eat and drink. I was having a dizzy spell from hunger and could not possibly make a decision on my own.  With Victoria's assistance, I choose the Toasty Pesto (pesto, fresh mozzarella, tomato, & spinach), and an amaretto flavored coffee which was perfectly sweetened and foamy. Also, a Berry Bananas smoothie (vanilla soy milk, almond butter, strawberries, blueberries, banana, & cinnamon) to take on the road with me back to Brooklyn.  My sister opted for the So Berry Fresh juice (blueberries, mint leaves, strawberries, & oranges) and Turkey Cheese & Greens sandwich (organic cream cheese, sprinkled black pepper, roasted turkey, cheddar, tomato, cucumber & kale).  Everything was SPECTACULAR. We sat and ate our sandwiches on the cute pea color chairs. The place is spotless, not one crumb in sight. I will drive to Washington Heights just to go eat at Green Juice Cafe.  LOVED IT!
